{"_header": true, "schema": "hexa-lang/roadmap/2", "name": "hexa-lang.stdlib", "mk": 2, "perspective": "peer", "perspective_note": "stdlib peer (top-level stdlib/ + self/stdlib/ + self/runtime/) — self-host stdlib basics 측 peer SSOT. 핵심 cond 측 .roadmap.hexa-lang cond.2 측 동일 surface, 측 peer view 측 추가 entry 측 모듈별 readiness audit.", "goal": "self-host stdlib (str/int/array/io + json/fs/parse/hash/optim/linalg/matrix/math/policy/cert/tokenize/net/test) 측 모듈별 native impl + selftest pass + cross-link to .roadmap.hexa-lang cond.2.", "required_conditions": ["RC1: self/stdlib/*.hexa (96 files) + stdlib/*/* (12 subdomains) 측 hexa-only impl (no python/c shell-out)", "RC2: 측 모듈별 selftest 측 PASS (자체 dogfood)", "RC3: cond cross-link 측 .roadmap.hexa-lang.cond.2 측 명시적 mirror"], "blockers": ["SB1: stdlib selftest aggregate dashboard 부재 (per-module 측 ad-hoc only)", "SB2: 측 size budget audit 측 stdlib total LoC 측 81792 lines 측 partition 측 audit 미수행"], "cross_link": [".roadmap.hexa-lang"], "status": "PROPOSED_PEER_SCAFFOLD", "since": "2026-05-02"}
{"id": "ST1", "kind": "audit", "title": "stdlib aggregate selftest dashboard 측 design", "rationale": "108개 module (96 self/stdlib + 12 stdlib/) 측 selftest 측 aggregate report 측 부재. CI gate 측 부재.", "weakest_link": "no aggregate dashboard", "status": "PROPOSED", "suggest_action": "tool/stdlib_selftest_aggregate.hexa 측 design — additive only, 기존 module touch 0", "loc_estimate": "150-250"}
{"id": "ST2", "kind": "audit", "title": "stdlib LoC partition + ownership map", "rationale": "81792 lines 측 single-bag — module 측 ownership/maintainer/last-touched 측 unknown. peer roadmap 측 bring visibility.", "weakest_link": "no ownership map", "status": "PROPOSED", "suggest_action": "scripts/stdlib_loc_audit.hexa 측 1-shot report — git log -1 + wc -l per file"}
{"id": "ST3", "kind": "cross_link", "title": ".roadmap.hexa-lang.cond.2 측 evidence backfill", "rationale": "cond.2 측 'stdlib basics self-hosted' status=unmet evidence=[] — peer 측 ST1 dashboard 측 evidence 측 attach 측 cond.2 status flip 측 가능", "weakest_link": "no evidence path", "status": "PROPOSED", "suggest_action": "ST1 PASS 후 .roadmap.hexa-lang cond.2 측 evidence array push (additive)"}
{"id": "F-STDLIB-T1", "kind": "feature", "title": "stdlib/tensor primitive module (shape + dtype + host buffer; matmul/add/relu; reshape/transpose/broadcast)", "rationale": "ML/DL upstack (nn.hexa, optim.hexa, self/ml/*) wants a single Tensor record; today every module hand-rolls flat array<float> + (m,n) tuples. Tensor record consolidates the boxing once and provides a stable seam for the BLAS/native dispatch path that the existing stdlib/linalg sister already pioneered.", "acceptance": "matmul(A:[M,K], B:[K,N]) -> [M,N] matches numpy reference within 1e-5 relative error on the documented oracle (2x2, 3x4*4x2, identity, 8x8 random) — codified in stdlib/tensor/test/tensor_matmul_test.hexa.", "files_added": ["stdlib/tensor/mod.hexa", "stdlib/tensor/shape.hexa", "stdlib/tensor/ops.hexa", "stdlib/tensor/ffi.hexa", "stdlib/tensor/dispatch.hexa", "stdlib/tensor/test/tensor_matmul_test.hexa"], "backend": "native (runtime `matmul` builtin = naive C kernel, self/runtime.c:7311) + opt-in BLAS via stdlib/linalg/sgemm (HEXA_TENSOR_BACKEND=blas; falls back to native when not detected). Detection: env-driven, mirrors stdlib/linalg/ffi.hexa rationale (symbol probing fragile across hxblas builds).", "status": "PROPOSED", "since": "2026-05-04"}
